    {
      "id": "IxOYhG3uofzTMNxXsI3Hz",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -6030.785793129074,
      "y": 1093.2354271592162,
      "width": 3242.0498046875,
      "height": 630,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "ae",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 34026391,
      "version": 32,
      "versionNonce": 905907383,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1760598152797,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "\n⏺ I can see the issue! The app is crashing with a type casting error in the state loading code. The error shows:\n\n  type 'List<String>' is not a subtype of type 'String?' in type cast\n\n  This is happening in IntervalTimerHomeState._loadState() at line 64, where it's trying to call getString() on a key that actually contains a List<String> (the presets list).\n\n  Let me fix this bug:\n\n⏺ Read(lib/state/interval_timer_home_state.dart)\n  ⎿  Read 30 lines\n\n⏺ I see the issue! The problem is that the app might have old data in SharedPreferences where presets was stored as a different type. The code looks correct, but we need to handle\n  the case where SharedPreferences might have stale data. Let me check if there's any issue with how the data is being saved/loaded:",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "\n⏺ I can see the issue! The app is crashing with a type casting error in the state loading code. The error shows:\n\n  type 'List<String>' is not a subtype of type 'String?' in type cast\n\n  This is happening in IntervalTimerHomeState._loadState() at line 64, where it's trying to call getString() on a key that actually contains a List<String> (the presets list).\n\n  Let me fix this bug:\n\n⏺ Read(lib/state/interval_timer_home_state.dart)\n  ⎿  Read 30 lines\n\n⏺ I see the issue! The problem is that the app might have old data in SharedPreferences where presets was stored as a different type. The code looks correct, but we need to handle\n  the case where SharedPreferences might have stale data. Let me check if there's any issue with how the data is being saved/loaded:",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
